comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASsdr8E1J", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 40, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8644849, "raw_content": "1.  He will do it by changing the value of the outstanding treasury bills ~70 cents on the dollar (this will knock 30% of the debt down to 28T)\r\n\r\n2. When people panic a dump treasuries Bessent will print 2T and purchase 4-5T and retire the bonds (It will cause some inflation, but the debt will drop further 3-4T to 25T)\r\n\r\n3. This will fuck the cities, democrat hell holes, the democrat union pensions and other democrat money holes that the democrats use to purchase voters.\r\n\r\n4. The cities will have to cut spending and benefit packages for teachers and other state government grifters (if they cut for cops, cops walk and then the cities become lord of the flies). The Democrat run cities own a disproportionate amount of treasuries and are the perfect places to eat the debt.\r\n\r\n5. He will argue Fraud has been an unfair burden on the American taxpayer, and we should not have to carry the future obligations through to the youth.\r\n\r\n6. He will argue to the globe that he solved (x) number of crises (Iran, Cuba, Isis, Abraham Accords, Maybe Ukraine, Venezuela, many of which will be resolved by next Feb 2027), and that the world owes some debt forgiveness.\r\n\r\n7. There will be a market correction when announced, it will be severe, then the U.S. will exist with ~25T in debt and lower debt service.  Boomer bonds will be impacted, but the overall impact will be lower than hyper-inflation and when the market corrects non-pavnicans will recover.\r\n\r\n8. Congress will be forced to reduce budget deficits (including debt service interest), to sub 500B deficits, 5T over ten years, 10T over twenty.\r\n\r\nAll of these actions will buy the U.S. 10-20 years of economic prosperity, with the potential for more if we can continue to elect MAGA patriots.\r\n\r\n*If something like this isn't the plan, then I don't see how we get past Hyper-inflation, I think much of what Trumps agenda has been is to get around congresses inaction on financial matters.  I would be surprised if the national debt isn't his end game, seeing as how he has managed debt his entire professional career, \r\n\r\n", "author": "zillat", "created": 1779980886113, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Ch3f4554551n", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Trump is going to drop the national debt by >12T, he will announce it at the next state of the union!", "last_comment_created": 1779988451645, "content": "<ol>\n<li>\n<p>He will do it by changing the value of the outstanding treasury bills ~70 cents on the dollar (this will knock 30% of the debt down to 28T)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>When people panic a dump treasuries Bessent will print 2T and purchase 4-5T and retire the bonds (It will cause some inflation, but the debt will drop further 3-4T to 25T)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>This will fuck the cities, democrat hell holes, the democrat union pensions and other democrat money holes that the democrats use to purchase voters.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>The cities will have to cut spending and benefit packages for teachers and other state government grifters (if they cut for cops, cops walk and then the cities become lord of the flies). The Democrat run cities own a disproportionate amount of treasuries and are the perfect places to eat the debt.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>He will argue Fraud has been an unfair burden on the American taxpayer, and we should not have to carry the future obligations through to the youth.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>He will argue to the globe that he solved (x) number of crises (Iran, Cuba, Isis, Abraham Accords, Maybe Ukraine, Venezuela, many of which will be resolved by next Feb 2027), and that the world owes some debt forgiveness.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>There will be a market correction when announced, it will be severe, then the U.S. will exist with ~25T in debt and lower debt service.  Boomer bonds will be impacted, but the overall impact will be lower than hyper-inflation and when the market corrects non-pavnicans will recover.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Congress will be forced to reduce budget deficits (including debt service interest), to sub 500B deficits, 5T over ten years, 10T over twenty.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>All of these actions will buy the U.S. 10-20 years of economic prosperity, with the potential for more if we can continue to elect MAGA patriots.</p>\n<p>*If something like this isn't the plan, then I don't see how we get past Hyper-inflation, I think much of what Trumps agenda has been is to get around congresses inaction on financial matters.  I would be surprised if the national debt isn't his end game, seeing as how he has managed debt his entire professional career,</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 28, "score_up": 40, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "2059711234723758379", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASsdr61pP", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 310, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8644077, "raw_content": "", "author": "5121313", "created": 1779940799289, "profile_picture": "zPB4r5jzErAy", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "God-is-good", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview"